<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196884>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Male Calopteryx splendens from Iran, above: Calopteryx s. orientalis (35.34757°N, 60.19286°E, Khorãsãn-e- Razavi, 1403 m, 10.VI.2016), middle: C. s. tschaldirica (Azarbãyejãn-e-Garbi, location 141), below: C. s. intermedia (Kermãnshãh, location114). Photos DI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196884/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196886>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Calopteryx splendens complex in NW-Iran: Different wing colourations in Calopteryx males from NW- Azarbãyejãn-e-Garbi (location 135), starting from hyaline wings on the left, typical tschaldirica, hybrid between tschaldirica and intermedia, to pure ntermedia on the right." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196886/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196888>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Male of Lestes macrostigma in NW-Azarbãyejãn-e-Garbi, location 124. Photo DI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196888/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196890>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Distribution of Sympecma fusca (dots), S. paedisca (triangles), and S. gobica (squares) in Iran. Closed symbols: records from 2010 onwards, open symbols: recordsbefore 2010." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196892>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Male appendices of the three Sympecma species: The position of the basal tooth on the appendix superior in comparison to the length of the appendix inferior is different. In S. gobica (mountain brook, Khorãsãn-e-Shomali) the basal tooth is located just on the end of the appendix inferior (A), in S. paedisca (Atrak River, Khorãsãn-e-Shomali) the appendix inferior ends before the basal tooth of the appendix superior (B), and in S. fusca (mountain brook, Azarbãyejãn-e-Garbi) the appendix inferior ends distal from the tooth of the appendix superior (C), (t—tooth, a—appendix inferior). Drawing OM." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196892/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196894>
    dc:description "FIGURE7. Male Ischnuraspecimens from Sistãn-va-Baluchestãn, above left: Ischnura forcipata (location 4), above right: I. senegalensis (location 16), below left: I.nursei (location 8), below right: I. rubilio (location 6). Photos DI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196894/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196896>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Male appendices from lateral view: A I. fountaineae, B I.evansi, C I. pumilio, D I. intermedia, E I. forcipata, and F I. senegalensis.Drawing OM." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196896/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196898>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Distribution of I. elegans (above, triangles), I. evansi (middle, dots), and I. fountaineae (below, squares) in Iran. Closed symbols:records from 2010 onwards, open symbols:records before 2010." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196900>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Distribution of Enallagma c. cyathigerum (dots) and Enallagma c. risi (triangles) in Iran. Closed symbols: records from 2010 onwards, open symbols: recordsbefore 2010." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196900/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196902>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Enallagma c. risi A, C (desert lake, Kermãn) and B, D Enallagma c. cyathigerum (Lake Valasht, Mazandarãn), male appendices from lateral and dorsal view.Drawing OM." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196902/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196904>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Males of left: Coenagrion lunulatum (Azarbãyejãn-e-Sharqi, location 131) and right: Coenagrion ponticum (Gilãn, location 77).Photos DI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196904/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196906>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Distribution of the members of the Coenagrion puella-group in Iran (C. puella (dots), C. ponticum (square), and C.australocaspicum (triangles) in Iran.Closed symbols: recordsfrom 2010 onwards, open symbols: records before 2010." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196906/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196908>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Coenagrion puella-group, male appendices in doral view of the three members of this group from Iran, from the left to the right:A: C. puella, B: C. ponticum, and C: C. australocaspicum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196908/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196910>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Males of left: Coenagrion pulchellum (Azarbãyejãn-e-Garbi, location 133) and right: Erythromma lindenii zernyi (Kordestãn, location 108). Photos DI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196910/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1196912>
    dc:description "FIGURE16.Male (PhotoDI) and itsappendix (in a lateral view,Photo TS) of Pseudagrion laidlawi25.75466°N, 61.46081°E, dam Sarbaz river, Sistãn-va-Baluchestãn (location 14), 17.IV.2015." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1196912/files/figure.png" ;
